                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.20/434</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-03-22">March 22,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President shares the views which you and I hold in this matter. This
                    Government cannot consider discussing the establishment of naval or air bases in
                    Liberia. We should inform the American Minister in Monrovia to say to the
                    Liberian Government that this Government sees no objection to the Liberian
                    Government discussing with the authorities in the French and British colonies
                    adjoining Liberia the formulation of plans and measures of a purely defensive
                    character.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
